</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Chin-Up Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong><strong>How To Do</strong></strong></h4>



<ol>
<li>Stand in front of a pull-up bar. Ensure your hips are facing forward with your hands by your sides.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Step onto the raised platform. Grip the pull-up bar using a double underhand grip, palms facing up. Your hands should be hip-width apart.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core. Step off the platform so your legs are dangling freely.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Exhale and pull your body up to the bar by flexing your elbows. Keep your elbows tucked at the front of your body.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Pause briefly once your chin reaches the bar.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale as you lower to the starting position under control.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Tips&nbsp;</strong></h4>



<ul>
<li>Ensure your elbows stay tucked at the front of your body throughout.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Keep your core engaged during the movement.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Make sure your body is still before beginning the chin-up.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Optimal Sets And Reps</strong></h4>



