</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Cross-Body Hammer Curl Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong><strong>How To Do</strong></strong></h4>



<ol>
<li>Start with your feet hip-width apart and your knees slightly bent. Using a neutral grip, hold two dumbbells by your sides, palms facing inward.</li>



<li>Inhale and brace your core. Exhale and bring one dumbbell across your body to chest height. Your elbows should stay in the same position.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Pause briefly at the top position. Inhale and lower the dumbbell back to the starting position under control.</li>



<li>Repeat with the other arm.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Tips</strong></h4>



<ul>
<li>Ensure you bring the dumbbell straight across your body while keeping your elbow in the same position.</li>



<li>Keep a neutral grip throughout the movement for targeted isolation.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Each dumbbell should come back to the same starting position.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Optimal Sets And Reps</strong></h4>



