<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">Anatomy Of The Back</h2>



<p>The <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK539746/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">back</a> is a large region of the body that runs from the neck to the glutes. It consists of the spine and two main back compartments.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The back performs several important functions. These include protecting the spinal cord, holding up the body and neck, and allowing movement of the limbs.&nbsp;</p>



<p>We can split the back muscles up into extrinsic and intrinsic components. The extrinsic back muscles produce shoulder movements and assist respiration (breathing). The intrinsic ones are found deeper in the body and act on the vertebral column (spine).&nbsp;</p>



<p>For the purpose of back and bicep workouts, we’re going to focus on the superficial muscles, or the ones you can see. These are the rhomboids, trapezius, and the latissimus dorsi.</p>


